Class Worksheet

  • java.lang.Object
    • at.ac.univie.swe2.SS2017.team403.Worksheet

  • public class Worksheet
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used to handle all operations connected to a worksheet. A worksheet-object contains either one or more cells and is part of a workbook.

      • getCell

        public Cell getCell(java.lang.String cellReferences,
                    Cell cellContext)
        This method is used to get a Cell which could contain references. We use the R1C1-notation, that means we have to split up the reference in two expressions. If there isn't any row reference we will take only the row-position. If there is a row reference which starts with a square bracket we will take the row-position and the complete formula. The same applies to columns. If there isn't any column reference we will take only the column-position. If there is a column reference which starts with a square bracket we will take the column-position and the complete formula.
        Parameters:
        cellReferences - cell-references
        cellContext - selected cell
        Returns:
        returns a cell with/without references
